cs.RO, cs.MA, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper presents a distributed algorithm for a group of robotic agents to deploy into environments with the objective of achieving full visibility coverage. 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is also likely as the paper deals with a group of agents working together to achieve a common goal. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the agents have omnidirectional vision and the objective is to achieve full visibility coverage. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with controlling the behavior of a group of agents to achieve a specific objective. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper presents an algorithm for partitioning the environment into distinct regions.
